CommonFields.Location: School of Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering, Queen's University Belfast, Belfast BT9 5AH, UK

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.EquipmentUsed: FEI Tecnai F20 field emission instrument

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.CycleInformation: 2920. The samples were allowed to equilibrate at 20 C before being heated at 10 C/min to 200 C, held at this temperature for 3 min, then cooled at 10 C/min to 20 C, held at 20 C for 1 min before being reheated at 10 C/min to 200 C again.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: X-Ray diffraction (WAXD) spectra of both the MWCNTs and the nanocomposites were recorded using a PANalytical X’Pert Pro diffractometer using Cu Ka radiation between 1 and 40 2theta.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Equipment: TA Instruments Hi-Res TGA 2950 thermogravimetric analyser
Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: from 20 to 500 C with a heating rate of 10 C/min. and a nitrogen gas flow rate of 40/60 cm3/min.

Raman_Spectroscopy.Description: Raman spectra were collected using a 785 nm (Titan sapphire laser), Jobin-Yvon HR640 spectrometer fitted with an Andor Technology CCD detector. The laser (50 mW) was line focussed onto the sample (100 um*4 mm) and was rotated throughout the experiment. No melting of the polymer was detected even after prolonged exposure under these conditions. Raman scattering was collected in a standard 180 degree backscattering geometry.

Rheometery.Description: The rheological behaviour of the composites was studied using an Ares (Rheometrics, Inc.) parallel-plate rheometer at 220 C, using dynamic oscillation frequency sweeps of 0.1–100 rad/s and back, in the linear-viscoelastic range (strain 2%) under a nitrogen atmosphere.

Electrometry.Description: Volume resistivity measurements were performed on samples of all composites that were firstly compression moulded into thin sheets (diameter 60 mm, thickness 0.35 mm). For high resistivity samples a Keithley electrometer (Model 6517A) equipped with a 8009 test fixture was used.

For more conductive samples (lower than 10^7 ohm-cm) strips with dimensions of 30*2 mm^2 were cut from the sheets and measured using a Keithley electrometer (Model DMM 2000) using a four-point test fixture (i.e. gold contact wires with a distance of 20 mm between source electrodes and 10 mm between the measuring electrodes).

temperature.description: unspecified, assumed to be room temperature
